# Patch 02: WAV File Retention
# Target: cli.py (in trnscrb package)
#
# PROBLEM:
# trnscrb deletes WAV audio files immediately after transcription.
# This prevents re-running diarization with improved models, and
# makes it impossible to recover if transcription quality was poor.
#
# CHANGE:
# 1. Find the line where the WAV file is deleted after transcription.
#    It will look something like:
#      os.unlink(wav_path)
#    or:
#      Path(wav_path).unlink()
#
# 2. Replace the unconditional delete with a config check:
#
#    keep_wav = os.environ.get("TRNSCRB_KEEP_WAV", "1") == "1"
#    if not keep_wav:
#        Path(wav_path).unlink(missing_ok=True)
#
# 3. Default to KEEPING the WAV (TRNSCRB_KEEP_WAV=1).
#    Users who want auto-deletion can set TRNSCRB_KEEP_WAV=0.
#
# WHY:
# Diarization models improve over time. Keeping the source audio lets
# you re-process old recordings with better speaker identification.
# Disk space is cheap; re-recording a call is impossible.
